**Finding the New Administrative Unit for "Xã Tịnh Ấn Tây"**

Okay, so I'm tasked with pinpointing the new administrative unit for the old address "Xã Tịnh Ấn Tây, Thành phố Quảng Ngãi, Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi".  My initial approach is to focus on the ward and province, since the district-level unit is usually eliminated in these situations.

First, I need to identify the obvious: "Xã Tịnh Ấn Tây" is the old ward, and "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi" is the province.  "Thành phố Quảng Ngãi" is a district level and so irrelevant to the core issue.

Now, I'll dive into the resolutions. My primary interest is in "60-NQ/TW: Các đơn vị hành chính cấp tỉnh mới sau sáp nhập, hợp nhất," to see if "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi" was affected. Thankfully, it states that "Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi" remains unchanged, even after potential mergers. Great, that simplifies things!

Next, I'll search the other resolutions.  And bingo! In "1677/NQ-UBTVQH15: Sắp xếp các đơn vị hành chính cấp xã của tỉnh Quảng Ngãi", line 82 jumps out at me. It explicitly states that "Xã Tịnh Ấn Tây" is merged with other wards to form "phường Trương Quang Trọng". This is exactly the information I was looking for!

To solidify this, I'll quickly check the "New wards" data.  I search for "phường Trương Quang Trọng" and find a matching entry: `{"ward_code":"21172","ward_name":"Phường Trương Quang Trọng","province_name":"Tỉnh Quảng Ngãi"}`. The province matches, confirming the findings.

My confidence is high on this.  The resolution provides a direct and clear mapping of the old ward to the new one. The new ward is also verified in the data with the correct province.
